Exampel for RESTTEMPLATE and WEBCLIENT

RESTTEMPLATE : RestTamplate is a synchronous (Blocking) HTTP client for consuming Rest API'S.
               if any request will send to the server it will wait until response come.And other thread will be in waiting state.


WEBCLIENT : Webclient is a asynchronous (non-blocking) reative Http client for consuming the Rest API's is introduce in spring 5.


  EXAMPLE :-

✅ Step 1: Add Dependency
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-webflux</artifactId>
</dependency>

✅ Step 2: Create WebClient Bean

@Configuration
public class WebClientConfig {

    @Bean
    public WebClient webClient() {
        return WebClient.builder()
                .baseUrl("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com")   // base url
                .build();
    }
}

✅ Step 3: Create DTO
@Data
@AllArgsConstructor
@NoArgsConstructor
public class Post {

    private Long userId;
    private Long id;
    private String title;
    private String body;
}
✅ Step 4: Create Service (CRUD Operations)
@Service
public class PostService {

    @Autowired
    private WebClient webClient;

    // 🔹 CREATE (POST)
    public Post createPost(Post post) {
        return webClient.post()
                .uri("/posts")
                .bodyValue(post)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(Post.class)
                .block();
    }

    // 🔹 READ (GET by id)
    public Post getPostById(Long id) {
        return webClient.get()
                .uri("/posts/{id}", id)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(Post.class)
                .block();
    }

    // 🔹 READ (GET all)
    public List<Post> getAllPosts() {
        return webClient.get()
                .uri("/posts")
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToFlux(Post.class)
                .collectList()
                .block();
    }

    // 🔹 UPDATE (PUT)
    public Post updatePost(Long id, Post post) {
        return webClient.put()
                .uri("/posts/{id}", id)
                .bodyValue(post)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(Post.class)
                .block();
    }

    // 🔹 DELETE
    public String deletePost(Long id) {
        webClient.delete()
                .uri("/posts/{id}", id)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(Void.class)
                .block();

        return "Deleted Successfully";
    }
}

🔥 Important Interview Point

You used:

bodyToMono() → Single object

bodyToFlux() → Multiple objects

.block() → Converts reactive to synchronous

If using full reactive app (WebFlux controller), then remove .block() and return Mono<Post> or Flux<Post>.

